The paper discusses the design and implementation of a control system for a robotic manipulator, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of machine learning algorithms for control also suggests the possibility of the paper belonging to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) category. The coordinated control of end-effector positioning and the use of force/position feedback constraints suggest the paper may also belong to the systems and control (cs.SY) category. The high level of dexterity provided for the operator suggests the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) category. Finally, the potential use of computer vision for the control system suggests the paper may also belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) category.
